68 /*========== Extern Constant and Variable Declarations ======================*/
69 /** Symbolic names for the possible states of the contactors */
70 typedef enum {
71  CONT_SWITCH_OFF, /*!< Contactor off --> Contactor is open */
72  CONT_SWITCH_ON, /*!< Contactor on --> Contactor is closed */
73  CONT_SWITCH_UNDEFINED, /*!< Contactor undefined --> Contactor state not known */
74 } CONT_ELECTRICAL_STATE_TYPE_e;
75 
76 /** Symbolic names defining the electric behavior of the contactor */
77 typedef enum {
78  CONT_FEEDBACK_NORMALLY_OPEN, /*!< Feedback line of a contactor is normally open */
79  CONT_FEEDBACK_NORMALLY_CLOSED, /*!< Feedback line of a contactor is normally closed */
80  CONT_FEEDBACK_THROUGH_CURRENT, /*!< Get feedback information through the current flowing into the contactor */
81  CONT_HAS_NO_FEEDBACK, /*!< Feedback line of the contactor is not used */
82 } CONT_FEEDBACK_TYPE_e;
83 
84 /** Contactor type */
85 typedef enum {
86  CONT_PLUS, /*!< Contactor is placed in HV plus path */
87  CONT_MINUS, /*!< Contactor is placed in HV minus path */
88  CONT_PRECHARGE, /*!< Contactor is used as precharge contactor, installed as a plus contactor */
89  CONT_UNDEFINED, /*!< Undefined contactor */
90 } CONT_TYPE_e;
91 
92 /**
93  * Some contactors are designed and optimized to open current that is flowing
94  * in one direction to provide maximum current breaking capability. This
95  * direction is then dependent on how the contactors are installed withing the
96  * battery system. If bidirectional contactors are used, the main power
97  * terminals can be connected in either direction and the current breaking
98  * capability is the same for both directions.
99  */
100 typedef enum {
101  CONT_CHARGING_DIRECTION, /*!< Contactor is preferred opened in charge current direction */
102  CONT_DISCHARGING_DIRECTION, /*!< Contactor is preferred opened in discharge current direction */
103  CONT_BIDIRECTIONAL, /*!< Contactor has no preferred way of being opened depending on the current flow */
104 } CONT_CURRENT_BREAKING_DIRECTION_e;
105 
106 /** Status struct for a registry of all contactors */
107 typedef struct {
108  CONT_ELECTRICAL_STATE_TYPE_e currentSet; /*!< current setpoint for the contactor */
109  CONT_ELECTRICAL_STATE_TYPE_e feedback; /*!< feedback from the contactor */
110  const CONT_FEEDBACK_TYPE_e feedbackPinType; /*!< type of feedback that the contactor uses */
111  const BS_STRING_ID_e stringIndex; /*!< index in which string the contactor is placed */
112  const CONT_TYPE_e type; /*!< type of contactor */
113  const SPS_CHANNEL_INDEX spsChannel; /*!< channel index of the SPS to which this contactor is connected */
114  const CONT_CURRENT_BREAKING_DIRECTION_e breakingDirection; /*!< preferred contactor opening direction */
115 } CONT_CONTACTOR_STATE_s;
116 
117 /** index number of the contactor array; not to be confused with #SPS_CHANNEL_INDEX */
118 typedef uint8_t CONT_CONTACTOR_INDEX;
119 
120 /** central state registry of all contactors of the system */
121 extern CONT_CONTACTOR_STATE_s cont_contactorStates[BS_NR_OF_CONTACTORS];
